description: Coefficients of Jacobi Eisenstein series of index 1 and weight 6.
references: M. Eichler and D. Zagier, The Theory of Jacobi Forms, Birkhauser, 1985, p. 141.
formula: t3^3*(t3^8-11*(t3^4*t2^4)/8+11*(t2^8)/32) where tj=theta_j(z) is associated weight 11/2 form - Kok Seng Chua (chuaks(AT)ihpc.nus.edu.sg), May 26 2000
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
